&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48660311</guid><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 14:16:40 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: Drip — pay-per-use finance newsletters for AI agents</title><link>https://dripstack.xyz/stock-picks</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi HN, I’m building Drip. It’s an API that lets AI agents access premium finance newsletters on a pay-per-use basis.&lt;p&gt;Agents will not subscribe to newsletters like humans do. A person subscribes for the ongoing relationship. An agent usually needs one narrower thing: the exact piece of research that helps answer a question right now.&lt;p&gt;We just launched a stock-picks endpoint for what many people are calling vibe investing / agentic investing. Using Drip, an agent can generate a cited report on the latest stock picks and recommendations from top premium finance writers.&lt;p&gt;You can generate a stock-picks report here: &lt;a href="https://dripstack.xyz/stock-picks" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://dripstack.xyz/stock-picks&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;Or give your agent access here: &lt;a href="https://dripstack.xyz/?tab=agents" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://dripstack.xyz/?tab=agents&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;Every time Drip answers a question, the authors whose work is referenced get paid on a pay-per-use basis.&lt;p&gt;This is early, and definitely not financial advice. I’d love feedback from anyone building agents, financial research tools, or trading workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
